-- Ford chief marketing officer to retire
-- 
-- Thu Nov 30, 2006 11:40am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2006/11/30/businesspro-ford-olsson-dc-idUSN3024366520061130

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - Ford Motor Co. ( F.N ) said on Thursday 
the automaker's chief marketing officer and nonexecutive 
chairman of Volvo Cars, Hans-Olov Olsson, will retire effective 
January 1, 2007. 

  Olsson, 64, is the latest executive to leave the automaker, 
which is in the midst of a sweeping restructuring in its North 
American operations.  Ford did not announce a replacement for the position of 
chief marketing officer but said Lewis Booth has been elected 
to replace Olsson as Volvo chairman.  Booth will continue in his role as executive vice 
president, Ford of Europe and Premier Automotive Group, Ford 
said.  Olsson was Ford's chief marketing officer for the past 
year, with responsibility for developing corporate marketing 
strategy for all of the company's brands.